data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async; in EF Core 11 that opt-in no longer exists. Every synchronous call (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) **always throws** — no workaround.

### Required fix — convert to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
        => await _context.Products.ToListAsync();

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
        => await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
        => await _context.Products.CountAsync();

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

All callers up the chain must also become `async`/`await`. There is no configuration flag to restore the old behavior.

**Two other Cosmos-specific changes** to watch for:
- **Empty owned collections** now return an empty collection instead of `null` — update any `is null` checks to `.Count == 0`.
- If you use **EF Core Tools**, the `Design` package is no longer transitive — add an explicit `PackageReference` if needed.
